David H. Clarke, president of Hanson Industries, this company's U.S. arm, and John G. Raos, a senior vice president of Hanson Industries, were elected executive directors of the parent's 10-member board.
Concurrently, John H. Pattisson, Sir Gordon Booth and Hugh G. Ashton resigned from the board, but remain officers of the London-based company.
Hanson also said Rudolph Agnew, former chairman of Consolidated Gold Fields PLC, recently purchased by Hanson, would join the board shortly.
Hanson has interests in chemicals, restaurants, foods, building products, cookware, lighting and other products. 

